  "response": "The main difference between Shure SE215-k and SE215-CL is primarily in their color and appearance:\n\n1. SE215-k (Black):\n- Black colored earphones\n- More discreet and professional look\n- Standard color variant\n\n2. SE215-CL (Clear):\n- Transparent/clear housing\n- Allows you to see the internal components and wiring\n- Same technical specifications and sound performance as the black version\n- Aesthetic preference for those who like seeing the inner workings\n\nBoth models share the same technical specifications:\n- Sound isolating design\n- Single dynamic MicroDriver\n- Frequency range: 22Hz - 18.5kHz\n- Impedance: 17 ohms\n- Detachable cable\n- Included accessories (carrying case, ear tips)\n\nThe choice between SE215-k and SE215-CL is mainly a matter of personal aesthetic preference, as the sound quality and performance are identical.",
